text: Maria Zhadan (born 6 February 1983) is a Russian volleyball player. She played at the 2005 Women's European Volleyball Championship, 2009 FIVB World Grand Prix, 2009 Women's European Volleyball Championship, and 2010 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship. She played for Zarechie-Odintsovo, Severyanka Cherepovets, WVC Dynamo Moscow, and Fakel Novy Urengoy. == References == Category:1983 births Category:Russian volleyball players Category:Living people
